  "text": "This report illustrated a novel needle deflection technique in vivo only using the steerable introducer for adjustment of the needle curve and subsequent successful radiofrequency perforation of the FO without mechanical force. Therefore, as with the standard radiofrequency transseptal puncutre, [CITATION_1] the radiofrequency needle using this technique can also provide safer and more effective TP compared to the conventional needle. In this case, the needle deflection in vivo could be achieved by the deflectable portion of the steerable introducer located at the curve segment of the TP needle ( Figure 2) . Therefore, given a steerable introducer with a certain degree of bending force, in situ needle deflection using the introducer can theoretically be obtained, to varying degrees. Other combinations of a radiofrequency needle and steerable introducer might be available for this technique.",
